response.question: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n). This represents the worst-case and average-case complexity. The best-case complexity is O(1).
response.feedback: Assessment: Correct. The student correctly identified the standard time complexity for linear search, which is O(n). This represents the upper bound (worst-case) where the algorithm may need to iterate through all 'n' elements.
